# Lariat Native Finalization

Use this rule when the task mentions Lariat Native, final macOS app, SwiftUI Lariat app, Phase C/D/E, H6/H7/H8, notarization, Xcode, native cutover, schema inversion, or service-day shutoff.

## Required Entry

Read `docs/LARIAT_NATIVE_FINAL_AGENT_GUIDE.md` before planning or editing.

Open the focused workspace:

- Cursor / Antigravity: `~/Dev/workspaces/lariat-native.code-workspace`
- Xcode: `~/Dev/workspaces/lariat-native.xcworkspace`

Do not open `~/` or bare `~/Dev`.

## Scope

- Canonical repo: `hospitality/Lariat/`
- Native package: `hospitality/Lariat/LariatNative/`
- Companion KDS repo: `Lariat-KDS/`
- Real data source corpus: `lariat-data-sources/` (read/ingest/reference only)

Top-level `Lariat/` is data artifacts, not the app repo.

## Completion Rules

- Do not re-port Phase A/B native waves. The current endgame doc records them complete.
- Do not flip schema ownership until C1-C4 gates are satisfied.
- Do not delete web write routes from unverified C1 ledger rows.
- Do not delete or move Lariat data/source roots without explicit user approval.
- H7a Phase 1 (13 `.safety`-tier files) is merged to `main`. H7a Phase 2 (~61 remaining files) has not started; create a fresh worktree/branch when picking it up rather than assuming one exists.

## Verification

- Native: `swift build && swift test` from `LariatNative/`
- KDS: `swift test` from `Lariat-KDS/`
- Web edge: relevant `npm run test:*`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build`
- Packaging: `LariatNative/Scripts/package-app.sh --pkg` plus codesign/resource checks

